{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"f6e9ac07-72ab-4a94-b5ea-bf3c795b7e5c","content":"You're on MSTest 3.8.2 which supports the modern approach. Here's the recommended pattern:\n\n```csharp\n[TestClass]\npublic class MyTests : IDisposable, IAsyncDisposable\n{\n    // TestContext is injected via constructor in MSTest 3.x\n    public TestContext TestContext { get; }\n\n    public MyTests(TestContext testContext)\n    {\n        TestContext = testContext;\n        // Synchronous initialization here\n    }\n\n    // For async initialization, implement IAsyncInitializable\n    // or use [TestInitialize]:\n    [TestInitialize]\n    public async Task SetupAsync()\n    {\n        // Async per-test initialization\n    }\n\n    [TestMethod]\n    public void SyncTest() { /* ... */ }\n\n    [TestMethod]\n    public async Task AsyncTest() { /* ... */ }\n\n    // Sync cleanup\n    public void Dispose() { /* ... */ }\n\n    // Async cleanup\n    public ValueTask DisposeAsync() { /* ... */ }\n}\n```\n\n**Key points for MSTest 3.x:**\n- **TestContext** is injected via the constructor (no more `[TestContext]` property setter).\n- Use the **constructor** for sync init and **`[TestInitialize]`** for async init.\n- Implement `IDisposable` / `IAsyncDisposable` for cleanup (preferred over `[TestCleanup]`).\n- Class-level fixtures use `[ClassInitialize]` (static) or `[AssemblyInitialize]`.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"7ff257c5-e35d-4d75-a7f7-8f0c08f24da8","outputTokens":370,"requestId":"BC50:D447C:1DEA976:212855E:69FA9725"},"id":"f9a79cca-9bee-474e-9bc8-866b8eb8fefc","timestamp":"2026-05-06T01:19:41.984Z","parentId":"41ba4af9-d11e-4013-b641-494d7669b6df"}
